      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just ads or relevant stuff though. like yesterday i typed \"the shadow in the\" and instead of suggesting \"shadow in the box\" or some movie title, it suggested \"the shadow in the architecture\". that makes zero sense for an ad or a trending search. it felt like it was reacting to a thought i hadn't even typed yet. don't you think it's weirdly specific, almost like something is actually watching the input stream and trying to communicate through the gaps?",
